org.dotplot.core.plugins
Class BatchJob

java.lang.Object
  org.dotplot.core.services.AbstractJob<IFrameworkContext>
      org.dotplot.core.plugins.BatchJob
All Implemented Interfaces:
IJob<IFrameworkContext>
public class BatchJob
extends AbstractJob<IFrameworkContext>

Instances of this class are Jobs for batch-processing.

Services are added by assigning their id to the BatchJob. This services are executed in order of their assignement.

Author:
Christian Gerhardt

addService

public void addService(java.lang.String serviceID,
                       int position)
Adds a serviceID to a certain position in the batch.

The serviceID currently holding the position will be moved up one position just as the ids above.

If position is greater then the current batchsize, the serviceID will be put on top of the batch.

Parameters:
serviceID - - the serviceID to put on the batch.
position - - the position to put the serviceID in the batch
